{
  "openapi": "3.0.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "API CRUD",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "description": "This is a simple CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) API for a task manager application, built with JavaScript and Express.\n\nIt allows clients to create, retrieve, update, and delete tasks via RESTful endpoints using standard HTTP methods.\n\nThe API is secured using an API key sent in the request headers to authenticate access.\n\nCORS middleware is used to handle cross-origin requests, and environment variables are managed with dotenv.\n\nTask data is stored in an in-memory SQLite database using the sqlite3 module.\n\nSwagger is integrated to provide automatic and interactive API documentation."
  },
